Creates a new PostgreHelper instance with direct PostgreSQL connection string.
Provides connection management and automatic resource cleanup.

Features:
- Direct connection string support
- Automatic connection opening
- Error logging
- Message customization
- Resource management

Example Request:


{
  "connectionString": "Host=localhost;Database=mydb;Username=user;Password=pass;Port=5432;Pooling=true;MinPoolSize=1;MaxPoolSize=100"
}



Example Usage:


// Basic connection
using var db = new PostgreHelper(
    connectionString: "Host=localhost;Database=mydb;Username=user;Password=pass"
);

// Advanced connection with options
using var dbAdvanced = new PostgreHelper(
    connectionString: "Host=localhost;Database=mydb;Username=user;Password=pass;Application Name=MyApp;Timeout=30",
    messages: new Messages(),
    logging: new SystemLogging()
);



> [!IMPORTANT]
