Provides functionality to generate API controllers and endpoints at runtime using a JSON configuration file. The configuration file should define: - API settings (method, route, tags, description) - Route parameters, query parameters, and request body - Database settings (engine, query type, return type) - Message templates for success/failure responses - Optional callback methods
