This class enables dynamic plugin loading, registration, and source code updates.




    var pluginManager = new Plugin();
    pluginManager.Register(sourceCodeDir: "wwwroot/plugins/source");

This method scans the directory for .cs files and loads plugins based on the provided
plugin names. If "All" is specified, all plugins are loaded.


PluginManager manager = new PluginManager();
manager.Initialize(sourceCodeDir: "C:\\Plugins", pluginNames: new[] { "All" });

This method clears the current list of active plugins and reloads plugins from the configured


source code path and plugin names.




    pluginManager.Reinitialize();

This method recompiles the plugin source code and replaces the loaded plugin type with the
newly compiled type.


var pluginManager = new PluginManager();
pluginManager.ReloadInstance(pluginName: "MyPlugin");

This method searches for the plugin type in the active plugins list using the specified


plugin name and returns a new instance of the plugin.


var instance = pluginManager.GetInstance(pluginName: "MyPlugin");

This method compiles the plugin source code and registers the plugin as active.




var pluginManager = new PluginManager();
pluginManager.Activation(pluginName: "MyPlugin");

This method searches for the plugin by name and deregisters it from the active plugins.




var pluginManager = new PluginManager();
pluginManager.Deactivation(pluginName: "MyPlugin");

This method writes the provided source code to the plugin's source file and triggers


recompilation to update the active plugin instance.


var pluginManager = new PluginManager();
pluginManager.SetSourceCode(pluginName: "MyPlugin", sourceCode: "public class MyPlugin {}");

This method extracts the plugin name from the source code, creates the source file in the


specified directory, and optionally activates the plugin.




PluginManager manager = new PluginManager();
manager.StoreNewPlugin(sourceCode: "public class MyPlugin {}", subDirectory: "Custom", activate: true);

This class enables dynamic plugin loading, registration, and source code updates.




    var pluginManager = new Plugin();
    pluginManager.Register(sourceCodeDir: "wwwroot/plugins/source");

This method removes the specified plugin from the active plugins list.


var manager = new PluginManager();
manager.DeregisterActivePlugin(plugin: myPlugin);

This method adds the specified plugin to the active plugins list if it is not already present.


var manager = new PluginManager();
manager.RegisterActivePlugin(plugin: myPlugin);

This method deregisters the current plugin and registers the new plugin.


var manager = new PluginManager();
manager.UpdateActivePlugin(currentPlugin: myOldPlugin, newPlugin: myNewPlugin);

This method is prepared for future development, such as decryption processes.


var manager = new PluginManager();
var code = manager.SourceCodeReader(filepath: ""plugin.cs"");

This method is prepared for future development, such as encryption processes.


var manager = new PluginManager();
manager.SourceCodeWriter(filepath: ""plugin.cs"", content: ""class A {}"");

This method compiles the specified C# source file and loads any plugin instances found.


